AccountId.Documentation: Account Id of the customer. It should be a 12 digit number.

BudgetName.Documentation: A string represents the budget name. No ":" character is allowed.

BudgetType.Documentation: The type of a budget. Can be COST or USAGE.

CalculatedSpend.Documentation: A structure holds the actual and forecasted spend for a budget.

ComparisonOperator.Documentation: The comparison operator of a notification. Currently we support less than, equal to and greater than.

CostFilters.Documentation: A map represents the cost filters applied to the budget.

CostTypes.Documentation: This includes the options for getting the cost of a budget.

CreationLimitExceededException.Documentation: The exception is thrown when customer tries to create a record (e.g. budget), but the number this record already exceeds the limitation.

DuplicateRecordException.Documentation: The exception is thrown when customer tries to create a record (e.g. budget) that already exists.

ExpiredNextTokenException.Documentation: This exception is thrown if the paging token is expired - past its TTL

GenericTimestamp.Documentation: A generic timestamp. In Java it is transformed to a Date object.

InternalErrorException.Documentation: This exception is thrown on an unknown internal failure.

InvalidNextTokenException.Documentation: This exception is thrown if paging token signature didn't match the token, or the paging token isn't for this request

InvalidParameterException.Documentation: This exception is thrown if any request is given an invalid parameter. E.g., if a required Date field is null.

MaxResults.Documentation: An integer to represent how many entries should a pagianted response contains. Maxium is set to 100.

NotFoundException.Documentation: This exception is thrown if a requested entity is not found. E.g., if a budget id doesn't exist for an account ID.

Notification.Documentation: Notification model. Each budget may contain multiple notifications with different settings.

NotificationThreshold.Documentation: The threshold of the a notification. It should be a number between 0 and 100.

NotificationType.Documentation: The type of a notification. It should be ACTUAL or FORECASTED.

NotificationWithSubscribers.Documentation: A structure to relate notification and a list of subscribers who belong to the notification.

NotificationWithSubscribersList.Documentation: A list of Notifications, each with a list of subscribers.

Spend.Documentation: A structure represent either a cost spend or usage spend. Contains an amount and a unit.

Subscriber.Documentation: Subscriber model. Each notification may contain multiple subscribers with different addresses.

SubscriptionType.Documentation: The subscription type of the subscriber. It can be SMS or EMAIL.

TimePeriod.Documentation: A time period indicated the start date and end date of a budget.

TimeUnit.Documentation: The time unit of the budget. e.g. weekly, monthly, etc.

errorMessage.Documentation: The error message the exception carries.

Documentation: All public APIs for AWS Budgets
